= colorpicker

This plugin lets the user easily pick a color via a graphical color selector.  
It uses the code developed by Matthias Platzer at:

http://www.knallgrau.at/code/colorpicker

with a couple of modifications:

1) pressing Esc while the dialog is open will cancel and reset the color to the original value before the dialog was opened

2) clicking outside of the dialog will close it and reset the color to the original value before the dialog was opened

== Usage

In the <head> section of the .rhtml file add the following:

<%= colorpicker_include_tag %>

In the <form> section add your colorpicker input tags like so:

<label for="organization_color_1">Color 1</label><br/>
<%= colorpicker_input_tag("organization", "color_1") %>

<label for="organization_color_2">Color 2</label><br/>
<%= colorpicker_input_tag("organization", "color_2") %>

<label for="organization_color_3">Color 3</label><br/>
<%= colorpicker_input_tag("organization", "color_3") %>

<label for="organization_color_4">Color 4</label><br/>
<%= colorpicker_input_tag("organization", "color_4") %>

At the end of the <body> section of the .rhtml file add the following:

<%= colorpicker_initialize(["organization_color_1", "organization_color_2", "organization_color_3", "organization_color_4"]) %>

== Resources

Install

* script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/colorpicker/trunk/colorpicker

Rubyforge project

* http://rubyforge.org/projects/colorpicker

